org.daisy.pipeline.modules

Class Module

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.daisy.pipeline.modules.Module

  • public abstract class Module
extends Object
    Daisy pipeline module holds a set of components accessible via their uri, its name, version and dependencies.

      • resolveDependencies

        public abstract void resolveDependencies()
        Called by ModuleRegistry to resolve dependencies of components. If a dependency of a component can not be resolved, this does not result in an exception, but the component will not be created (and consequently will not be available through the #getComponent() or getEntity(java.lang.String) method).

      • getResource

        public URL getResource(String path)
                throws NoSuchFileException
        Get the specified resource from the module. This includes all resources, also the ones that are not exposed as components. The method can be overridden to exclude certain resources that have unmet dependencies.
        Parameters:
        path - The (not URL-encoded) path, relative to catalog.xml, of a resource inside the JAR or class directory of the module.
        Returns:
        An encoded absolute URL
        Throws:
        NoSuchFileException - if the resource at path is not available

      • hasComponent

        public boolean hasComponent(URI uri)
        Whether this module provides a component with the given URI. This assumes that the component can be resolved. If the component could not be resolved (e.g. due to a missing dependency), this will result in a ResolutionException when the getComponent(java.net.URI) method is called.

      • getComponents

        public Set<URI> getComponents()
        Gets all the component URIs.

      • getComponent

        public Component getComponent(URI uri)
                       throws NoSuchElementException,
                              ResolutionException
        Gets the component identified by the given URI.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if this module provides a component with the given URI.
        ResolutionException - if the component could not be resolved, e.g. due to a missing dependency.

      • hasEntity

        public boolean hasEntity(String publicId)
        Whether this module provides a entity with the given ID. This assumes that the entity can be resolved. If the entity could not be resolved (e.g. due to a missing dependency), this will result in a ResolutionException when the getEntity(java.lang.String) method is called.
